# Unity Folders
# https://git-scm.com/docs/gitignore
# A leading slash matches the beginning of the pathname.

# Would like to keep /Logs/ untracked to remove, but since 2020 Unity will keep /Logs/ contents opened and unable to remove
/Logs/
/Temp/
/Builds/
/Library/
# Added in Unity 2020, shall be ignored according to Aras
# https://forum.unity.com/threads/whats-the-usersettings-directory.754436/#post-5029937
/UserSettings/

# Unity Generated Solution files
/*.sln
/*.csproj

# Visual Studio DB
/.vs/

# ReSharper Personal Config
/*.DotSettings.user

# Visual Studio Code
/.vscode/
/obj/

# Rider
.idea/
/Assets/Plugins/Editor/JetBrains/
/Assets/Plugins/Editor/JetBrains.meta

# MonoDevelop
/*.userprefs

# Windows File Explorer Thumbnail Cache
Thumbs.db
# Mac Finder Cache
.DS_Store
# These should be ignored by default global gitignore, but from time to time we got these from packages or other sources



# Wwise
# https://blog.audiokinetic.com/version-control-a-wwise-project/
/.backup/
/.cache/

*.akd

*.validationcache
*.wsettings

IncrementalSoundBankData.xml
Assets/Test.meta
Assets/Test/
WwiseProject/SPARTA/.cache
Assets/Wwise/Editor/ProjectData/AkWwiseProjectData.asset
WwiseUnityIntegration_Mac_Src.zip
Assets/InitTestScene******************.unity.meta
Assets/InitTestScene******************.unity

*.prof
